This paper deals with the technical and procedural complexities of Spectrum Access System (SAS)-based sharing framework, which falls under the domain of network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also involves the analysis of census data and the exploration of census tract boundaries, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the licensing scheme, which can be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
